1
00:00:01,240 --> 00:00:05,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Why does Goryoukaku take 
the shape of a star?</font>

2
00:00:05,570 --> 00:00:08,040
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The answer is: for war.</font>

3
00:00:08,040 --> 00:00:10,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It was based on the design 
of the bastion fort,</font>

4
00:00:10,530 --> 00:00:16,490
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">which was invented in Europe while 
Japan was in the Muromachi period.</font>

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:20,490
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The place we're standing 
on is the bastion.</font>

6
00:00:20,930 --> 00:00:23,700
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">From this location, for instance,</font>

7
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:28,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">we have a clear view of that bridge 
and the stone wall behind it,</font>

8
00:00:28,130 --> 00:00:31,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">along with the bridge 
and the bastion wall.</font>

9
00:00:32,460 --> 00:00:35,190
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The bastion wall on the right, as well.</font>

10
00:00:35,190 --> 00:00:39,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We can strike approaching enemies 
from the side and eliminate them.</font>

11
00:00:40,050 --> 00:00:41,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I see.</font>

12
00:00:41,570 --> 00:00:44,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">By deploying troops in each bastion,</font>

13
00:00:44,810 --> 00:00:50,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">we can attack our foes in any 
direction, without any blind spots.</font>

14
00:00:51,100 --> 00:00:54,200
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The shape of the fortress 
is specialized for war.</font>

15
00:00:54,530 --> 00:00:57,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But we can't use it like this.</font>

16
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:58,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We need trenches.</font>

17
00:00:59,140 --> 00:01:00,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Indeed.</font>

18
00:01:00,790 --> 00:01:05,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Those who have experienced the new 
age of war understand such things.</font>

19
00:01:06,360 --> 00:01:09,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">While we wait for Sofia 
and her men to arrive,</font>

20
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:13,260
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">we will search for the gold 
and prepare for combat.</font>

21
00:02:21,340 --> 00:02:28,290
<font size="40"><b>Golden Kamuy</b></font>

22
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:49,290
<font face="Times New Roman" size="12" color="#62000d"><b>{\an3}Episode Fifty-Nine
Our Kamuy</b></font>

23
00:02:52,410 --> 00:02:53,650
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I found something!</font>

24
00:02:55,330 --> 00:02:56,830
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A rock, huh?</font>

25
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm exhausted.</font>

26
00:03:02,340 --> 00:03:07,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm pretty sure they hid it 
in the moat, not a building.</font>

27
00:03:07,470 --> 00:03:11,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But the old man said, "Dig here, doggy."</font>

28
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:14,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You've got something that makes 
you think it's here, right?</font>

29
00:03:15,750 --> 00:03:19,620
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You're still hiding things 
from us at this point?</font>

30
00:03:19,620 --> 00:03:21,970
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm not one of your soldiers, you know!</font>

31
00:03:27,070 --> 00:03:30,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I found a lot of sandbags in a storehouse.</font>

32
00:03:32,050 --> 00:03:32,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Huh?</font>

33
00:03:33,310 --> 00:03:34,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They're here!</font>

34
00:03:46,830 --> 00:03:56,500
<font face="Times New Roman" size="20"><b>{\an8}<font color="#141410"><font size="30">God</font></font></b></font>

35
00:03:47,070 --> 00:03:50,630
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The character for god on my tattoo.</font>

36
00:03:50,990 --> 00:03:56,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">When we laid out the code, it landed 
right on the storehouses here.</font>

37
00:03:57,150 --> 00:04:00,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There must be something buried here.</font>

38
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:10,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Another rock, huh?</font>

39
00:04:11,150 --> 00:04:15,060
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Does the god character 
really mean anything?</font>

40
00:04:16,090 --> 00:04:17,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">No idea...</font>

41
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:20,530
<font face="Times New Roman" size="20"><b>{\an8}<font color="#151410">God</font></b></font>

42
00:04:18,070 --> 00:04:19,850
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But the fact is,</font>

43
00:04:19,850 --> 00:04:23,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">there's no other character with a 
similar reading, like shin or jin.</font>

44
00:04:23,780 --> 00:04:26,280
<font face="Times New Roman" size="24"><b>3:30 AM</b></font>

45
00:04:31,710 --> 00:04:32,930
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's not a rock!</font>

46
00:04:35,830 --> 00:04:37,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I found something!</font>

47
00:04:39,010 --> 00:04:40,380
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Just this box?</font>

48
00:04:40,380 --> 00:04:43,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There must be more buried below 
it, obviously! You idiot!</font>

49
00:04:43,470 --> 00:04:46,260
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Open it up already! Hurry!</font>

50
00:04:48,130 --> 00:04:50,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What's this? Soil? Sand?</font>

51
00:04:52,370 --> 00:04:53,310
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Cietoi.</font>

52
00:04:53,830 --> 00:04:56,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Powdered diatomaceous earth.</font>

53
00:04:56,020 --> 00:04:57,850
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That can't be all that's here!</font>

54
00:04:59,740 --> 00:05:00,890
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What's this?</font>

55
00:05:01,300 --> 00:05:02,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Paper?</font>

56
00:05:03,510 --> 00:05:05,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">An animal stomach.</font>

57
00:05:05,610 --> 00:05:07,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We use them for holding
oils and other things.</font>

58
00:05:08,340 --> 00:05:11,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So they've done everything they can 
to make sure the contents stayed dry.</font>

59
00:05:13,410 --> 00:05:14,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A book?</font>

60
00:05:14,660 --> 00:05:16,380
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What does it say?</font>

61
00:05:16,380 --> 00:05:18,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Let the old men read it!</font>

62
00:05:20,650 --> 00:05:21,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What's this?</font>

63
00:05:22,290 --> 00:05:24,190
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Land deeds.</font>

64
00:05:25,060 --> 00:05:27,970
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">About the time our deal with 
the Russian navy broke down,</font>

65
00:05:27,970 --> 00:05:32,930
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">a government called the 
"Ezo Republic" existed in Hakodate.</font>

66
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:36,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They needed money to fight.</font>

67
00:05:37,010 --> 00:05:43,030
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So we met with a Nispa named Enomoto 
Takeaki from the Ezo Republic,</font>

68
00:05:43,030 --> 00:05:49,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and traded gold for a treaty 
recognizing Ainu land rights.</font>

69
00:05:50,020 --> 00:05:52,240
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Land deeds bought with the gold?</font>

70
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:55,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Where's the land? How big is it?</font>

71
00:05:56,410 --> 00:05:57,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Look at this.</font>

72
00:05:57,640 --> 00:06:01,630
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Vast tracts of land, 
spread all throughout Hokkaido.</font>

73
00:06:02,350 --> 00:06:05,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There's no way Hijikata Toshizou 
wouldn't know about this.</font>

74
00:06:05,940 --> 00:06:07,830
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I didn't, actually.</font>

75
00:06:08,150 --> 00:06:13,260
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">About the time this treaty was 
made, I was busy fighting.</font>

76
00:06:13,260 --> 00:06:16,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I spent very little time at Goryoukaku.</font>

77
00:06:16,610 --> 00:06:21,190
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Just as we were about to hand over the 
gold, the Hakodate War came to an end,</font>

78
00:06:21,550 --> 00:06:24,150
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and the Ezo Republic ceased to exist.</font>

79
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:26,550
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But Enomoto-san worked with the</font>

80
00:06:26,550 --> 00:06:30,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Meiji government to ensure the treaty
with the Ainu would remain enforced.</font>

81
00:06:31,460 --> 00:06:35,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The Meiji government wanted 
the gold too, so they agreed.</font>

82
00:06:35,450 --> 00:06:39,540
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They assumed, foolishly,
 that they could abrogate it later.</font>

83
00:06:39,820 --> 00:06:44,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But Enomoto-san had actually 
had the ambassadors</font>

84
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,000
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="20"><b>{\an8}<font color="#1a1818">Netherlands</font></b></font>

85
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:46,760
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="20"><b>{\an8}<font color="#1a1818">France</font></b></font>

86
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:48,360
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="20"><b>{\an8}<font color="#1a1818">England</font></b></font>

87
00:06:44,430 --> 00:06:48,970
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">of six countries be 
present for its signing.</font>

88
00:06:45,130 --> 00:06:48,970
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="20"><b>{\an8}<font color="#1a1818">America</font></b></font>

89
00:06:46,670 --> 00:06:48,970
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="20"><b>{\an8}<font color="#1a1818">Italy</font></b></font>

90
00:06:48,260 --> 00:06:48,970
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="20"><b>{\an8}<font color="#1a1818">Prussia</font></b></font>

91
00:06:49,310 --> 00:06:52,490
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It was clearly made out to 
be an international treaty,</font>

92
00:06:52,490 --> 00:06:56,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">one that could not be easily abandoned.</font>

93
00:06:56,500 --> 00:07:00,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Perhaps this was his way of repaying 
the Ainu for their support of him,</font>

94
00:07:00,510 --> 00:07:02,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">or perhaps he knew the war was lost,</font>

95
00:07:02,390 --> 00:07:06,480
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and only wanted to make one last 
problem for the government.</font>

96
00:07:06,770 --> 00:07:10,490
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The deed book contains a detailed 
record of its own history,</font>

97
00:07:10,490 --> 00:07:16,970
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and entrusts the landowners, 
the Ainu, to decide how the land is used.</font>

98
00:07:17,890 --> 00:07:21,920
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The Meiji government wouldn't 
want this getting out.</font>

99
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:27,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Wait, does this mean the gold is gone?!</font>

100
00:07:27,380 --> 00:07:28,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Wonderful.</font>

101
00:07:29,220 --> 00:07:33,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">My daughter will live as an Ainu, and 
this is the greatest gift I can give her.</font>

102
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:37,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I thought that this was 
all we could do, too.</font>

103
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:41,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That the only thing we could do with 
the gold was buy forested land.</font>

104
00:07:42,010 --> 00:07:45,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That this was the only way to 
protect the Ainu without fighting.</font>

105
00:07:47,430 --> 00:07:49,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If we protect the forests, 
we can protect the kamuy.</font>

106
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:53,280
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Our culture can't exist
 without the kamuy.</font>

107
00:07:54,180 --> 00:07:58,920
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The thing I had finally figured out, 
what I could do for the Ainu...</font>

108
00:08:00,580 --> 00:08:06,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The old Ainu had already accomplished it!</font>

109
00:08:06,850 --> 00:08:09,710
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The golden kamuy that I was 
told would bring disaster...</font>

110
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:13,950
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">was the kamuy we really needed!</font>

111
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:19,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm so disappointed I can't even stand.</font>

112
00:08:22,260 --> 00:08:26,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But why'd Wilk hide the deed book here?</font>

113
00:08:26,570 --> 00:08:28,190
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">He could've taken it with him.</font>

114
00:08:28,580 --> 00:08:31,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Perhaps someone was after it.</font>

115
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:32,320
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Kiroranke, maybe?</font>

116
00:08:33,380 --> 00:08:35,030
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But stealing the book wouldn't...</font>

117
00:08:35,030 --> 00:08:39,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Wilk's code led me to the deed book.</font>

118
00:08:40,270 --> 00:08:45,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But there was nothing in our 
discussion about protecting forests.</font>

119
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:52,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Did the Ainu make the land treaty to 
protect their forests in the first place?</font>

120
00:08:53,030 --> 00:08:58,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Leaving behind the Kamuy wouldn't 
make the Ezo Republic more powerful.</font>

121
00:08:58,470 --> 00:09:02,060
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Don't you think Wilk left 
this behind because he wanted</font>

122
00:09:02,330 --> 00:09:04,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">the land's resources to be developed?</font>

123
00:09:06,300 --> 00:09:07,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Asirpa...</font>

124
00:09:07,750 --> 00:09:11,370
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What Wilk said... What Yulbars said...</font>

125
00:09:11,770 --> 00:09:13,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Forget it all.</font>

126
00:09:14,260 --> 00:09:15,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Sofia.</font>

127
00:09:17,660 --> 00:09:19,830
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There's nothing left for us here.</font>

128
00:09:21,340 --> 00:09:25,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We have two hours until Lieutenant 
Tsurumi and his men arrive.</font>

129
00:09:25,530 --> 00:09:26,830
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We need to get out of here now!</font>

130
00:09:27,350 --> 00:09:30,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We need to tell the ones 
working on our defenses!</font>

131
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:32,630
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hurry! Kantarou, head 
to the east entrance!</font>

132
00:09:36,490 --> 00:09:38,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm crying so much I can't see.</font>

133
00:09:38,790 --> 00:09:40,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I can't walk.</font>

134
00:09:40,140 --> 00:09:41,890
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hang in there, Shiraishi.</font>

135
00:09:42,220 --> 00:09:45,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hijikata Nispa. I'll take the book.</font>

136
00:09:47,630 --> 00:09:49,150
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hijikata Nispa?</font>

137
00:09:50,470 --> 00:09:52,860
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Only half was used!</font>

138
00:09:56,980 --> 00:10:03,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It says that 37,125 kilograms of 
gold were given to Enomoto Takeaki.</font>

139
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:08,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Nopperabo told me there 
was 75,000 kilograms.</font>

140
00:10:09,510 --> 00:10:13,710
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So a bit over half of 
it's still out there?</font>

141
00:10:13,710 --> 00:10:17,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Half the gold's still out there somewhere!</font>

142
00:10:16,270 --> 00:10:17,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Calm down, Shiraishi!</font>

143
00:10:22,370 --> 00:10:23,760
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Get to the trenches!</font>

144
00:10:28,690 --> 00:10:30,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Lieutenant Tsurumi's men?</font>

145
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:31,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But it's too soon!</font>

146
00:10:31,850 --> 00:10:33,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Look out at the sea.</font>

147
00:10:33,300 --> 00:10:34,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Something's in the sky.</font>

148
00:10:34,820 --> 00:10:36,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Military air balloons!</font>

149
00:10:36,750 --> 00:10:38,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They're watching us?</font>

150
00:10:38,950 --> 00:10:41,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So that was gunfire from a ship?!</font>

151
00:10:42,470 --> 00:10:44,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They came in their destroyers!</font>

152
00:10:44,910 --> 00:10:48,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>The minute Lieutenant Tsurumi 
began to crack the code,</i></font>

153
00:10:48,730 --> 00:10:52,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>he also contacted Ominato 
naval base in Aomori,</i></font>

154
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:53,580
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>where Koito's father was located,</i></font>

155
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:54,460
<font face="Times New Roman" size="20"><b><font color="#030003">Ominato</font></b></font>

156
00:10:53,580 --> 00:10:56,550
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>so that he could quickly get to 
the gold no matter where it was.</i></font>

157
00:10:56,550 --> 00:11:02,490
<font face="Times New Roman" size="20"><b>{\an8}<font color="#000003">Sapporo</font></b></font>

158
00:10:56,550 --> 00:11:03,240
<font face="Times New Roman" size="20"><b>{\an7}<font color="#000300"><font size="15">Sugimoto Route (Hakodate Line)</font></font></b></font>

159
00:10:56,900 --> 00:11:00,630
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>He went from Sapporo Station 
to Muroran station,</i></font>

160
00:10:57,480 --> 00:11:03,570
<font face="Times New Roman" size="20"><b>{\an5}<font color="#000003">Muroran</font></b></font>

161
00:10:57,480 --> 00:11:04,050
<font face="Times New Roman" size="20"><b>{\an9}<font color="#000300"><font size="15">Tsurumi Muroran Line)</font></font></b></font>

162
00:11:00,630 --> 00:11:06,060
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>and took a destroyer waiting 
at the port to Hakodate port!</i></font>

163
00:11:02,070 --> 00:11:04,050
<font face="Times New Roman" size="20"><b>{\an4}<font color="#000003">Hakodate</font></b></font>

164
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,050
<font face="Times New Roman" size="20"><b>{\an5}<font color="#000003">Ominato</font></b></font>

165
00:11:08,170 --> 00:11:09,060
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yes!</font>

166
00:11:10,340 --> 00:11:12,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Good morning!</font>

167
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:18,070
<font size="40"><b><font color="#d6a42f">Golden Kamuy</font></b></font>

168
00:11:22,270 --> 00:11:23,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What's he doing?</font>

169
00:11:27,810 --> 00:11:29,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Kadokura! Take care of the rest!</font>

170
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:31,580
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Where's he going?</font>

171
00:11:35,870 --> 00:11:37,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Somebody's here.</font>

172
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:40,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Don't shoot! I want to 
talk to Lieutenant Tsurumi.</font>

173
00:11:40,530 --> 00:11:43,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Did he go to surrender on his own?</font>

174
00:11:43,780 --> 00:11:45,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Of course not!</font>

175
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:47,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Probably not.</font>

176
00:11:47,700 --> 00:11:50,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Anyway, it's too late to retreat.</font>

177
00:11:51,070 --> 00:11:52,970
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We'll have to fight as best we can.</font>

178
00:11:52,970 --> 00:11:54,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Let's go, Kirawus.</font>

179
00:11:57,690 --> 00:12:01,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Is their plan to use those big 
cannons to flatten Goryoukaku?</font>

180
00:12:01,730 --> 00:12:03,320
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We need to get out of here.</font>

181
00:12:03,630 --> 00:12:08,950
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They're lying in wait to attack 
anyone who runs from the cannons.</font>

182
00:12:09,310 --> 00:12:10,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">This place has three exits,</font>

183
00:12:10,910 --> 00:12:15,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and I'm sure they have lots of 
soldiers hidden beyond the bridges.</font>

184
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:18,960
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Only 16 army soldiers can 
ride along on a destroyer.</font>

185
00:12:19,290 --> 00:12:22,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Even if they brought all four 
destroyers that we saw at Abashiri,</font>

186
00:12:22,410 --> 00:12:23,510
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">that's 64 people.</font>

187
00:12:24,020 --> 00:12:27,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They may not have many stationed 
except at the exits!</font>

188
00:12:27,050 --> 00:12:30,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">All the more reason to leave now, then.</font>

189
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:31,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">No, wait!</font>

190
00:12:31,670 --> 00:12:35,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Wilk said the prisoners 
would get half the gold!</font>

191
00:12:36,040 --> 00:12:42,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Let's figure out if the other half 
is in Goryoukaku before we run!</font>

192
00:12:42,690 --> 00:12:46,580
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Indeed... after all these 
complicated riddles,</font>

193
00:12:46,580 --> 00:12:51,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">he can't have hidden it 
somewhere else in Hokkaido.</font>

194
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:55,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I can't die before I see 
the gold for myself!</font>

195
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:56,540
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Calm down, Shiraishi!</font>

196
00:12:58,330 --> 00:13:00,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The cannon fire stopped.</font>

197
00:13:01,290 --> 00:13:03,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There was no gold.</font>

198
00:13:03,820 --> 00:13:07,760
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I wondered what the famous Nagakura 
Shinpachi was going to say.</font>

199
00:13:08,020 --> 00:13:12,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Do you expect me to say, 
"Oh, too bad, then," and just go home?</font>

200
00:13:13,890 --> 00:13:19,850
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I can simply use my destroyers' 
cannons to blow you all to pieces,</font>

201
00:13:19,850 --> 00:13:22,070
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">sweep aside the pile of gore,</font>

202
00:13:22,330 --> 00:13:24,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and see for myself whether it's there.</font>

203
00:13:24,850 --> 00:13:29,070
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We found the deed to land in Hokkaido, 
which the Ainu bought with gold.</font>

204
00:13:31,070 --> 00:13:35,040
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The result of a treaty between 
the Ainu and Ezo Republic.</font>

205
00:13:35,420 --> 00:13:38,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If you were an intelligence officer, 
you should know something about this.</font>

206
00:13:38,790 --> 00:13:44,420
<font face="Times New Roman" size="20"><b>{\an8}<font color="#242424">Ministry of Finance          Home Ministry</font></b></font>

207
00:13:39,450 --> 00:13:41,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">About how the Meiji government</font>

208
00:13:41,170 --> 00:13:44,890
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">seemed to have a lot of extra 
money after the Battle of Hakodate.</font>

209
00:13:44,890 --> 00:13:49,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Or something that didn't make 
sense about the huge cost of the</font>

210
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Russo-Japanese War.</font>

211
00:13:51,450 --> 00:13:55,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The deed book says that the 
Ainu have the right to use</font>

212
00:13:55,170 --> 00:13:57,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">their land as they see fit.</font>

213
00:13:57,550 --> 00:14:00,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It has the rights to a huge 
expanse of Hokkaido land.</font>

214
00:14:00,700 --> 00:14:04,760
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The forests can be turned into 
fertile land, perfect for farming,</font>

215
00:14:04,760 --> 00:14:07,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and vast mineral resources 
sleep beneath them...</font>

216
00:14:08,070 --> 00:14:09,480
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And the name on the deed?</font>

217
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:10,370
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">None.</font>

218
00:14:10,700 --> 00:14:15,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It simply says the Ainu have the right 
to use the land, and no one else.</font>

219
00:14:15,110 --> 00:14:19,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But it's worth something to you, as well.</font>

220
00:14:19,430 --> 00:14:24,920
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The 7th has many Ainu soldiers, 
like Ariko Ipopte, right?</font>

221
00:14:26,990 --> 00:14:31,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Please, spare the lives of everyone 
in exchange for the deed book.</font>

222
00:14:31,580 --> 00:14:36,310
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hijikata Toshizou is driven 
by one thing: battle.</font>

223
00:14:36,690 --> 00:14:38,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">As the second in command 
of the Shinsengumi,</font>

224
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:43,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">he's looking for a place to have 
one last grand battle and die.</font>

225
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:50,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">He was lucky enough to survive 
the hopeless Battle of Hakodate.</font>

226
00:14:50,160 --> 00:14:53,990
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But now he's eager to find a place to die.</font>

227
00:14:54,220 --> 00:14:59,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I promise I'll go back to Goryoukaku 
and persuade him to surrender.</font>

228
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:05,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Nagakura-san, please, get off the ground.</font>

229
00:15:05,560 --> 00:15:11,070
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You're hoping to use the deed book 
to get me to stop firing the cannons,</font>

230
00:15:11,070 --> 00:15:16,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">then go back to Goryoukaku and fight 
alongside Hijikata Toshizou, right?</font>

231
00:15:16,910 --> 00:15:18,980
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You cunning old man.</font>

232
00:15:19,530 --> 00:15:23,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You, Nagakura Shinpachi, are more eager 
to have one last fight than anyone!</font>

233
00:15:23,940 --> 00:15:27,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You're a survivor of 
those crazy Shinsengumi!</font>

234
00:15:28,610 --> 00:15:31,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Stop with the bad acting.</font>

235
00:15:31,900 --> 00:15:35,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm good at seeing through people's lies.</font>

236
00:15:37,810 --> 00:15:41,370
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Then did you figure out how 
much of what I said was true?</font>

237
00:16:04,620 --> 00:16:08,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Lieutenant Tsurumi's men who couldn't 
fit on the destroyers</font>

238
00:16:08,350 --> 00:16:10,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">will be coming here by train, right?</font>

239
00:16:10,740 --> 00:16:12,990
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They should be here any minute.</font>

240
00:16:13,260 --> 00:16:15,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The cannon fire's stopped.</font>

241
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:18,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Why don't we at least get 
the young lady out of here?</font>

242
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:22,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">She can take the deed book, too.</font>

243
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Sounds good to me.</font>

244
00:16:23,590 --> 00:16:27,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That book's not going to 
do me a damn bit of good.</font>

245
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:29,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Don't you all agree?</font>

246
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:31,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We've finally made it all this way,</font>

247
00:16:31,430 --> 00:16:34,260
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and the gold might be beneath our feet!</font>

248
00:16:34,490 --> 00:16:36,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I can't just give up!</font>

249
00:16:39,870 --> 00:16:41,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'll stay here too.</font>

250
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:44,890
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I want to be useful to everyone, 
and I have to see this to the end.</font>

251
00:16:46,620 --> 00:16:47,710
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Young lady.</font>

252
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:54,650
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If it looks bad, I'll get 
Asirpa-san somewhere safe.</font>

253
00:16:55,370 --> 00:16:56,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hijikata-san!</font>

254
00:16:57,590 --> 00:17:00,540
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Nagakura-san let himself be caught!</font>

255
00:17:00,540 --> 00:17:03,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">He told me to "take care of the rest"!</font>

256
00:17:03,290 --> 00:17:08,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It might be thanks to him 
that the attacks stopped.</font>

257
00:17:08,550 --> 00:17:11,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Anyway, I'll follow the plan.</font>

258
00:17:23,710 --> 00:17:25,980
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Okay, hurry and go.</font>

259
00:17:26,690 --> 00:17:28,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Please, stay safe.</font>

260
00:17:32,410 --> 00:17:35,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Let's go, Kirawus! Mansur!</font>

261
00:17:36,620 --> 00:17:40,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If you sent Kadokura on 
that suicide mission,</font>

262
00:17:40,250 --> 00:17:43,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">then it means we're staying 
here to fight, right?</font>

263
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:44,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Why?</font>

264
00:17:44,820 --> 00:17:51,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Asirpa, staying will teach 
you what your father felt.</font>

265
00:17:52,060 --> 00:17:56,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A wind of fortune brought 
to us by a very lucky man</font>

266
00:17:56,600 --> 00:18:00,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">is about to bring us victory.</font>

267
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:06,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Wow, lots of flies today.</font>

268
00:18:06,100 --> 00:18:08,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Those aren't flies, Kadokura!</font>

269
00:18:11,650 --> 00:18:13,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The soldiers who came by train!</font>

270
00:18:13,750 --> 00:18:17,650
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A minute later and we'd have 
been completely surrounded.</font>

271
00:18:24,610 --> 00:18:29,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So it was thanks to you 
that the cannons stopped.</font>

272
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:32,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I don't know how long it will last.</font>

273
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:36,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But I've left a seed that will 
make Lieutenant Tsurumi hesitate about</font>

274
00:18:36,610 --> 00:18:39,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">doing any large-scale attacks.</font>

275
00:18:40,490 --> 00:18:43,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We brought Onuma dumplings, the famous 
snack from Onuma Park Station.</font>

276
00:18:44,580 --> 00:18:45,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A deed book?</font>

277
00:18:45,930 --> 00:18:47,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You believe this?</font>

278
00:18:47,790 --> 00:18:48,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's a bluff!</font>

279
00:18:49,060 --> 00:18:51,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We can't be so sure.</font>

280
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:56,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The Meiji government should have been
 flat broke after the Battle of Hakodate,</font>

281
00:18:56,670 --> 00:19:00,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">but they immediately began the grand 
redevelopment of Tokyo, the new capital.</font>

282
00:19:00,890 --> 00:19:06,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A water and sewage system. The large-scale
railways. The brick town of Ginza.</font>

283
00:19:06,450 --> 00:19:10,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And the huge beer factories 
built in Yokohama, Sapporo,</font>

284
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:14,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Tokyo, and Osaka, one after another.</font>

285
00:19:14,670 --> 00:19:19,260
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They say the liquor tax alone was enough 
to pay for the Sino-Japanese War.</font>

286
00:19:19,650 --> 00:19:21,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The Russo-Japanese War was</font>

287
00:19:21,010 --> 00:19:24,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">also supposedly paid for with huge 
loans from foreign countries.</font>

288
00:19:24,340 --> 00:19:26,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But who knows if that's true.</font>

289
00:19:26,330 --> 00:19:31,630
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Before the war, not a single 
country expected Japan to win.</font>

290
00:19:32,020 --> 00:19:34,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But there's no way General Okuda 
wouldn't have known about it.</font>

291
00:19:35,160 --> 00:19:38,620
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Does this mean his goal was to get rid of 
this unfortunate contract with the Ainu,</font>

292
00:19:38,620 --> 00:19:42,380
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and he simply used the 
gold as bait for us?</font>

293
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:47,620
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Well, I'll see for myself if 
the deed book is even real.</font>

294
00:19:47,890 --> 00:19:52,370
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'll give Hijikata Toshizou 
the fight he wants.</font>

295
00:19:53,990 --> 00:19:57,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's time for the Battle of Goryoukaku.</font>

296
00:19:57,790 --> 00:19:59,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Dig around here.</font>

297
00:19:59,840 --> 00:20:01,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Why here?</font>

298
00:20:01,090 --> 00:20:07,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Kadokura's tattoos had an 
important clue that led us here.</font>

299
00:20:07,430 --> 00:20:11,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It was so long ago that even 
I'd forgotten about it.</font>

300
00:20:12,770 --> 00:20:14,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They can't see us from 
those balloons, right?</font>

301
00:20:14,660 --> 00:20:17,070
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The pine trees hide us perfectly.</font>

302
00:20:19,820 --> 00:20:20,650
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hurry!</font>

303
00:20:26,310 --> 00:20:27,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A lid?</font>

304
00:20:27,080 --> 00:20:30,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Open it, now! Now!</font>

305
00:20:35,820 --> 00:20:37,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A well for horses.</font>

306
00:20:37,990 --> 00:20:44,510
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm probably the only man 
alive today who remembers it.</font>

307
00:20:47,760 --> 00:20:49,580
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's dangerous! Calm down!</font>

308
00:20:49,580 --> 00:20:51,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Calm down, Shiraishi! You're crazy!</font>

309
00:20:52,860 --> 00:20:56,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Asirpa-san, let's go down together.</font>

310
00:20:57,310 --> 00:20:58,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yeah.</font>

311
00:21:02,650 --> 00:21:03,650
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Well?</font>

312
00:21:06,930 --> 00:21:08,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There are bags everywhere!</font>

313
00:21:11,420 --> 00:21:13,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Let's open one in front of everyone!</font>

314
00:21:13,820 --> 00:21:16,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Okay, pull it up, Ushiyama!</font>

315
00:21:18,750 --> 00:21:19,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Gold!</font>

316
00:21:22,780 --> 00:21:24,540
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I told you, that's dangerous!</font>

317
00:21:24,540 --> 00:21:26,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Just wait up there, fool!</font>

318
00:21:26,250 --> 00:21:28,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Ow...</font>

319
00:21:54,810 --> 00:21:55,930
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Asirpa-san...</font>

320
00:21:56,650 --> 00:22:00,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Looks like we found the gold, huh?</font>

321
00:23:35,120 --> 00:23:40,250
<font face="Times New Roman" size="12" color="#62000d"><b>{\an3}<font size="17">Next Time
<font size="27">The Battle of Goryoukaku</font></font></b></font>

322
00:23:35,850 --> 00:23:40,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Next Time: The Battle of Goryoukaku!</i></font>

